The paper deals with query evaluation on probabilistic databases, which is a topic closely related to databases and logic. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses treewidth, which is a graph parameter, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions OBDDs and DNNFs, which are data structures used in computational complexity and artificial intelligence, respectively, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) possible sub-categories.
